title: Jaisen Clifford
content:
Jaisen Jaren Clifford (born 4 February 1996) is a South African soccer player who plays as a forward for Bulgarian club Sportist Svoge.

In 2015, Clifford signed for Maltese second tier side Gudja United.[1] In 2017, he signed for Stumbras in the Lithuanian top flight, helping them win the 2017 Lithuanian Football Cup, their only major trophy.[2] In 2019, he signed for Portuguese third tier club Condeixa.[2] Before the second half of 2020–21, Clifford signed for Cape Town All Stars in the South African second tier, where he made 5 appearances and scored 1 goal.[2] On 4 February 2021, he debuted for Cape Town All Stars during a 3–1 win over Bizana Pondo Chiefs.[2] On 4 February 2021, Clifford scored his first goal for Cape Town All Stars during a 3–1 win over Bizana Pondo Chiefs.[2] Before the second half of 2021–22, he signed for Armenian team Van.[3]
